-- Polish Stocks Advance to One-Month High on Stimulus Hopes
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-06-12T14:00:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/polish-stocks-advance-to-one-month-high-on-stimulus-hopes.html
Polish stocks rose, sending the
benchmark gauge to a one-month high as speculation the U.S.
Federal Reserve will take steps to stimulate the world’s largest
economy tempered concern that European debt crisis will worsen.  The WIG20 Index climbed 2 percent to 2,208.24 at 3:40 p.m.
in Warsaw, the strongest level since May 7 on a closing basis.
The index has rallied 8.3 percent in four days, compared with a
2.9 percent advance in the MSCI  Emerging Markets  Index.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA, the copper producer with the biggest
European mine output, jumped to almost two-month high and PKN
Orlen SA, the country’s biggest refiner led gains as copper and
oil rebounded in New York.  Fed Bank of Chicago President  Charles Evans  said he would
support a variety of measures to generate faster job growth,
underscoring his preference for more stimulus. The Fed is
scheduled to meet next week as slowing job growth at home and a
deepening crisis in  Europe  weigh on the outlook.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
